.TH "kernel_connect" 9 "kernel_connect" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
kernel_connect \- connect a socket (kernel space)
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" kernel_connect
.BI "(struct socket *sock "  ","
.BI "struct sockaddr *addr "  ","
.BI "int addrlen "  ","
.BI "int flags "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "sock" 12
socket
.IP "addr" 12
address
.IP "addrlen" 12
address length
.IP "flags" 12
flags (O_NONBLOCK, ...)

For datagram sockets, \fIaddr\fP is the addres to which datagrams are sent
by default, and the only address from which datagrams are received.
For stream sockets, attempts to connect to \fIaddr\fP.
Returns 0 or an error code.
